	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note66" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Strabo/17A1*.html#ref66
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">66</A>
Both the text and the interpretation are doubtful. <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">á½Î´Î¿Î¯</SPAN> ("streets") is not found in the <SPAN CLASS="small">MSS.</SPAN>; but, although it is the <I>natural</I> word to supply, just as <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">á½Î´ÏŒÏ‚</SPAN> <I>must</I> be supplied above with <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">Ï€Î»Î±Ï„Îµá¿–Î±</SPAN> ("broad"), it hardly suits the context, as Kramer, who conjectures <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">ÎºÎ±Ï„Î¿Î¹ÎºÎ¯Î±Î¹</SPAN> ("settlements"), insists. Vogel (see critical note) simply emends <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">á¼„Î»Î»Î±Î¹</SPAN> ("other") to <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">á¼…Î»Î±Î¹</SPAN><A CLASS="correction"
onMouseOver="return Ebox('The Loeb edition<BR>has '+BadF+'á¼„Î»Î±Î¹'+CloseF+'',WIDTH,120)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Âº</A> ("salt-works").

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
		<P CLASS="b0 a0 justify">
The critical note to the Greek text (<SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">Î±á¼± Ï€Î±ÏÎ±ÎºÎµÎ¯Î¼ÎµÎ½Î±Î¹ á¼„Î»Î»Î±Î¹</SPAN>) reads:
		<P CLASS="i1 b0 a0 justify">
<SPAN CLASS="manuscript">D</SPAN>Â (?) and the editors before Kramer add <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">Î±á¼±</SPAN> before <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">á¼„Î»Î»Î±Î¹</SPAN>. Kramer conj. that <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">ÎºÎ±Ï„Î¿Î¹ÎºÎ¯Î±Î¹</SPAN>, or some word of similar meaning, has fallen out after <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">á¼„Î»Î»Î±Î¹</SPAN>. Meineke conj. <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">ÎºÎ±Î»Î¹Î±Î¯</SPAN> ("wooden dwellings"), Vogel <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">á¼…Î»Î±Î¹</SPAN> ("salt-works"), for <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">á¼„Î»Î»Î±Î¹</SPAN>.
	</P></DIV>


